"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964297","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-09-11","<p>The Ministry of Justice has recently conducted a procurement competition relating to the provision of HMCTS Approved Enforcement Agency services, including bail, no bail and arrest warrants. The conduct and outcome of that process is currently subject to legal proceedings. As a result, the Ministry of Justice has not yet entered into any new contract(s) for AEA services with bidders. Accordingly, pending the resolution of the legal proceedings, it would not be appropriate to comment on the contents of any of the bids received as the final outcome of the procurement competition remains undetermined.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-09-11T15:52:55.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964297/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964297/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964297/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-09-03","Arrest Warrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department has accepted bids relating to the outsourcing of bail, no bail and breach arrest warrants from providers that offered to provide those services for free; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","169175"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964298","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-09-06","<p>On 29 June 2018 it was confirmed by BAE Systems that the contract that had been signed with the State of Qatar on 10 December 2017 for 24 Typhoon aircraft had been amended to include the supply of nine Hawk.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-09-06T16:07:43.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964298/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964298/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964298/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-09-03","Qatar: Hawk Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 26 February 2018 to Question 128885, if he will provide an update on progress on the potential order by the Qatari Government of Hawk aircraft.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","169213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964299","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-09-06","<p>The Secretary of State for Defence and the Amir of Qatar discussed the strength of our bilateral defence and security relationship and the unique opportunities associated with Qatar's recent acquisition of Typhoon and Hawk aircraft.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-09-06T16:06:59.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964299/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964299/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964299/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-09-03","Qatar: Hawk Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he had with the Amir of Qatar at their meeting on 24 July 2018 on the potential order of Hawk aircraft by the Qatari Government.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","169214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964300","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-09-11","<p>Our current planning assumption remains that we will procure the Joint Land Tactical Vehicle to meet the Army's requirement for a future protected multi-role vehicle. Funding has been set aside for this acquisition in the Department's Equipment Plan. A final decision to proceed will not be taken until the Modernising Defence Programme has been completed and our wider plans for Armed Forces modernisation are fully mature.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-09-11T14:32:57.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964300/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964300/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964300/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-09-03","Army: Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent progress has been made on package one of the Multi-Role Vehicle - Protected programme.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","169215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964301","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-09-06","<p>For Operational security reasons the Royal Navy will not release minimum staffing level requirements.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-09-06T15:17:01.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964301/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964301/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964301/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-09-03","Warships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the minimum staffing level requirement is for each vessel in the Royal Navy surface fleet.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","169216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964302","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-09-11","<p>The Army is in the process of assessing its future artillery system capability requirement for the Armoured Infantry and Strike Brigades. It has established a programme, known as Mobile Fires Platform, to refine the requirement and modernise the capability.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-09-11T14:36:20.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964302/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964302/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964302/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-09-03","Artillery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent assessment his Department has made of the artillery system requirement to support the Strike brigades.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","169217"
