"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964438","Home Office","false","2018-09-10","<p>The Department spent £70 million during the financial year 2017-18 as per our accounts. For the financial year 2018-19, the Department has received an allocation of £395 million from HM Treasury to continue preparing for the UK to leave the EU.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-09-10T18:34:55.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964438/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964438/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964438/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-09-03","Home Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the total cost to the public purse for his Department’s work preparing of the UK to leave the EU has been since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","168898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964439","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-09-11","<p>Work relating to the UK leaving the EU, is an all-of-government operation. Members of staff across the Department provide advice and analysis on EU Exit issues as required. But, given the interactions between EU Exit work and the departments other priorities, it would not be possible to give an accurate figure of cost.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-09-11T16:07:41.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964439/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964439/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964439/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-09-03","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what the total cost to the public purse for his Department’s work preparing for the UK to leave the EU has been since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","168899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964440","Cabinet Office","false","2018-09-10","<p>HM Treasury has allocated over £2 billion of additional funding to departments and the Devolved Administrations for EU exit preparations so far. This breaks down as:</p><p> </p><p>- £412m of additional funding over the spending review period for the Department for Exiting the European Union, Department for International Trade and the Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office at Autumn Statement 2016.</p><p> </p><p>- £286m of additional funding for 17/18 (a full breakdown of which can be found in Supplementary Estimates 17/18).</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/679738/PU2137_Supplementary_estimates_web.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/679738/PU2137_Supplementary_estimates_web.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p>- Over £1.5bn of additional funding for 18/19. A full breakdown of which can be found in the Chief Secretary’s Written Ministerial Statement, HCWS540, laid on the 13th March. (<a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2018-03-13/HCWS540/" target="_blank">https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2018-03-13/HCWS540/</a>)</p><p> </p><p>At Autumn Budget 2017, the Chancellor also set aside £1.5 billion of additional funding for EU Exit preparations in 2019/20. Departments will be invited to bid for 2019/20 EU Exit preparation funding later in the year. Details of timings and process will be announced in due course.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","168921","2018-09-10T15:04:01.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964440/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964440/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964440/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-09-03","Cabi