"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964451","Department for International Trade","false","2018-09-11","<p>The Department was created in July 2016 following the result of the EU referendum and was specifically established as part of the government's EU exit strategy.</p><p>At Autumn Budget 2017, the Chancellor also set aside £1.5 billion of additional funding for EU Exit preparations in 2019/20. Departments will be invited to bid for 2019/20 EU Exit preparation funding later in the year. Details of timings and process will be announced in due course.</p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery",,"2018-09-11T12:05:28.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964451/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964451/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964451/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-09-03","Department for International Trade: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what estimate he has made of the cost to his Department of leaving the EU in accordance with (a) the proposals set out in the Government’s White Paper and (b) a no-deal scenario.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","168911"
